where Q is an integer, R is an integer between 0 and B-1</li></ul></div></d=
iv></div><div class=3D"clearfix"><div class=3D"perseus-renderer perseus-ren=
derer-responsive"><div class=3D"paragraph" data-perseus-paragraph-index=3D"=
0"><div class=3D"paragraph">The first two properties let us find the GCD if=
 either number is 0. The third property lets us take a larger, more difficu=
lt to solve problem, and <strong>reduce it to a smaller, easier to solve pr=
oblem</strong>.</div></div></div></div><div class=3D"clearfix"><div class=
=3D"perseus-renderer perseus-renderer-responsive"><div class=3D"paragraph" =
data-perseus-paragraph-index=3D"0"><div class=3D"paragraph">The Euclidean A=
lgorithm makes use of these properties by rapidly reducing the problem into=
 easier and easier problems, using the third property, &nbsp;until it is ea=
sily solved by using one of the first two properties.</div></div></div></di=
v><div class=3D"clearfix"><div class=3D"perseus-renderer perseus-renderer-r=
esponsive"><div class=3D"paragraph" data-perseus-paragraph-index=3D"0"><div=
 class=3D"paragraph">We can understand why these properties work by proving=
 them.</div></div></div></div><div class=3D"clearfix"><div class=3D"perseus=
-renderer perseus-renderer-responsive"><div class=3D"paragraph" data-perseu=
s-paragraph-index=3D"0"><div class=3D"paragraph">We can prove that GCD(A,0)=
=3DA is as follows:</div></div></div></div><div class=3D"clearfix"><div cla=
ss=3D"perseus-renderer perseus-renderer-responsive"><div class=3D"paragraph=
" data-perseus-paragraph-index=3D"0"><ul><li>The largest integer that can e=
venly divide A is A.</li><li>All integers evenly divide 0, since for any in=
teger, C, we can write C =E2=8B=85 0 =3D 0. So we can conclude that A must =
evenly divide 0.</li><li>The greatest number that divides both A and 0 is A=
.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class=3D"clearfix"><div class=3D"perseus-=
renderer perseus-renderer-responsive"><div class=3D"paragraph" data-perseus=
-paragraph-index=3D"0"><div class=3D"paragraph">The proof for <strong>GCD(0=
,B)=3DB</strong> is similar. (Same proof, but we replace A with B).</div></=
div></div></div><div class=3D"clearfix"><div class=3D"perseus-renderer pers=
eus-renderer-responsive"><div class=3D"paragraph" data-perseus-paragraph-in=
dex=3D"0"><div class=3D"paragraph">To prove that <strong>GCD(A,B)=3DGCD(B,R=
)</strong> we first need to show that <strong>GCD(A,B)=3DGCD(B,A-B)</strong=
>.</div></div></div></div><div class=3D"clearfix"><div class=3D"perseus-ren=
