ustrating the properties of the greatest common divisor (GCD). The leftmost=
 section shows two columns labeled A and B with stacked rectangles represen=
ting the GCD of A and B. The subtraction of the two columns (A minus B) equ=
als a smaller column labeled C, which is also represented as the GCD of A a=
nd B. The middle section shows the addition of column C to column B to form=
 a larger column labeled A, with the property that the GCD of B and C equal=
s the GCD of B and (A minus B). The rightmost section includes a key where =
blue rectangles represent &quot;less than or equal to,&quot; red rectangles=
